FBIS4-68140 "jptot020__l94062" JPRS-TOT-94-020-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 9 May 1994 WEST EUROPE TURKEY `Sound Bombs' at Istanbul Train Station; No Casualties `Sound Bombs' at Istanbul Train Station; No Casualties TA0905082394 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 0700 GMT 9 May 94 TA0905082394 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Announcer-read report over video] [Text] Two sound bombs were thrown underneath one of the coaches of the blue train at Haydarpasa Station in Istanbul last night. No one was killed or injured in the incident. According to information received from Istanbul Security Directorate officials, at 2330 last night, unidentified persons threw two sound bombs under the blue train scheduled to leave Istanbul for Ankara at 2345. The noisy explosion of the bombs caused panic among the passengers waiting to board the train. Bomb experts who arrived at the scene of the incident found and defused a time bomb ready for explosion in one of the coaches. The blue train eventually left for Ankara at 0110.
